struct task_struct {
    //        (   )
    struct thread_info		thread_info;
    unsigned int			__state;
    /* -  priority... */
    int				prio;
    int				static_prio;
    int				normal_prio;

    /* Real parent process: */
    struct task_struct __rcu	*real_parent;  //  1
    /* Recipient of SIGCHLD, wait4() reports: */
    struct task_struct __rcu	*parent;  //  2

    pid_t				pid;
    unsigned int			policy;

    /*
     * Children/sibling form the list of natural children:
     */
    struct list_head		children;
    struct list_head		sibling;
};

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <pthread.h>

void *myThreadFun(void *vargp)
{
    printf("THREAD pid: %d\n", getpid());
    sleep(5);
    return NULL;
}

int main()
{
    printf("PROCESS pid: %d\n", getpid());
    pthread_t thread_id;
    pthread_create(&thread_id, NULL, myThreadFun, NULL);
    sleep(5);
    pthread_join(thread_id, NULL);
    exit(0);
}

void do_smth() {
    pid_t pid = fork();
    
    if (pid == 0) {
        printf("I am child: %d\n", getpid());
        fflush(stdout);
        _exit(0);
    } else {
        printf("I am parent: %d\n my child pid is: %d\n", getpid(), pid);
        fflush(stdout);
    }
}

void spawn_then_wait() {
    pid_t pid = fork();
    
    if (pid == 0) {
        long_work();
        printf("Child death\n");
        fflush(stdout);
        _exit(0);
    } else {
        //  ...
        waitpid(pid, NULL, 0);
        printf("Parent death\n");
        fflush(stdout);
    }
}

void do_tests() {
    pid_t pid;
    int status;
    
    pid = fork();
    if (pid == 0) _exit(0);
    status = 0;
    waitpid(pid, &status, 0);
    printf("exit_success: %d\n", WEXITSTATUS(status));
    
    
    pid = fork();
    if (pid == 0) _exit(123);
    status = 0;
    waitpid(pid, &status, 0);
    printf("exit_success: %d\n", WEXITSTATUS(status));
    
    
    pid = fork();
    if (pid == 0) _exit(123456);
    status = 0;
    waitpid(pid, &status, 0);
    printf("exit_success: %d\n", WEXITSTATUS(status));
    
    
    pid = fork();
    if (pid == 0) _exit(-10);
    status = 0;
    waitpid(pid, &status, 0);
    printf("exit_success: %d\n", WEXITSTATUS(status));
}

do_tests();
